perl-libconfig (1.1.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix set_hook/get_hook to use config-level API instead of setting-level on root
  * Fix get_item zero-value bug by restructuring with config_setting_get_elem + type check
  * Fix auto_check_and_create strrchr -> strchr for correct nested path resolution
  * Add bindings: set_destructor, set_include_func, set_fatal_error_func, setting get_elem/set_hook/get_hook
  * Add Devel::CheckLib configure-time check for libconfig
  * Clean up dead commented-out code blocks
  * Add tests for get_elem, setting set_hook/get_hook, invalid boolean input

 -- Cnangel <cnangel@gmail.com>  Tue, 20 May 2026 10:00:00 +0800

perl-libconfig (1.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix version guards for multi-version libconfig compatibility (1.1.x ~ 1.8.x)
  * Fix config_setting_lookup_int type for pre-1.4 (long* vs int*)
  * Fix config_setting_source_file, config_set_default_format, config_setting_lookup guards
  * Fix config_set_hook to use config_setting_set_hook
  * Add version guards for error_type/error_file (1.4+)

